+is+one+of+the+most+effective+ways+to+mitigate+acute+distress.+Explaining+that+you+will+not+be+doing+%e2%80%9ctherapy.%e2%80%9d%0d%0a++++++++3.+Assess+what+is+going+on+with+the+peer+and+the+severity+of+their+distress%2c+including+whether+they+are+able+to+function.+Use+active+and+reflective+listening%3b+it+helps+mitigate+some+of+the+distress+just+to+feel+heard.++%0a++++++++4.+Provide+interventions%c2%a0that+are+based+on+what+you+learn+about+your+peer+during+the+assessment.+Examples+used+in+this+case+include+helping+your+peer+think+about+their+thoughts+and+feelings+and+come+up+with+solutions+themselves%2c+encouraging+social+support%2c+normalizing+their+distress%2c+and+paving+the+way+to+get+help+if+needed.+%0a++++++++5.+Provide+resources%c2%a0on+how+to+get+help%2c+including+for+mental+health%2c+in+case+your+peer+needs+them+currently+or+later.+%0d%0a++++++++6.+Follow+up+by+checking+with+your+peer+again+after+a+few+days.+Even+if+they+seem+stable+currently%2c+they+may+need+help+later.+Also%2c+a+second+connection+provides+another+experience+of+social+support.+Further+connection+can+lead+to+confusion+between+peer+support+and+a+clinical+relationship.+%0d%0a++++++++7.+Recommend+further+assistance+as+needed%2c+if+the+peer+is+experiencing+dysfunction+in+their+lives+in+terms+of+mental+health+problems+or+inability+to+fulfill+responsibilities%2c+or+feels+the+need+for+further+supportive+contacts.+%0a</value></values></panel></panels></tab><tab id="gw"><type>Textbox</type><name>Bibliography</name><panels><panel id="ll"><type>TextboxPanel</type><values><value id="CustomContentValue">Everly+GS%2c+Lating+JM.+The+Johns+Hopkins+Guide+to+Psychological+First+Aid.+Vol+1+edition.+Baltimore%3a+Johns+Hopkins+University+Press%3b+April+1%2c+2017%0a%0aMiller+A.+CBT+for+Front-Line+Medical+Professionals%3a+Brief+Interventions+During+a+Time+of+Crisis.+April+4%2c+2020.+Beck+Institute+for+Cognitive+Behavior+Therapy.%0a%0aNational+Cancer+Institute.+Body+%26+Soul.+Peer+Counselor+Training.+2006.%0a%0aWas